<2ND_LINE>AM-Aliens Overboard,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Aliens Jump Ship In Front Of Coast Guard Station</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A group of Dominicans apparently trying
to sneak into the United States picked the wrong place to jump
ship, splashing into the water in front of the Coast Guard station,
an official said.
   ``The barge was inbound to Miami when 12 people jumped overboard
and swam for shore opposite the Coast Guard base, not the best of
all possible places,'' said Coast Guard Chief Lou Parris. ``Two
off-duty (guardsmen) were fishing on the docks opposite the base
and spotted the swimmers.''
   Five of the men were captured Saturday, still swimming, and were
turned over to the Immigration and Naturalization Service.
   The seven others from the Dominican-registered barge and tugboat
scrambled ashore in an area lined with freight docks and were at
large late Saturday, Parris said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
