<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Murder-Racial     07-17 0438</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Murder-Racial,0454</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Charged In Killing, Racial Motive Discounted</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents of 8th graf</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By ANNE RUTH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>KINGSTON, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police charged a black man with murdering
a black woman that investigators thought was possibly racially
motivated because the letters ``KKK'' were carved on her leg.
   Detective Mike Turck said Sunday that any racial motive in the
death of Anna Kithcart, 19, had been ruled out and that a drug link
was suspected.
   Police arrested Jeffrey Allen Dawson, 29, late Saturday. He
appeared before a City Court judge Sunday, but his arraignment was
postponed until Monday after he asked for an attorney. No bond was
set and he remained in jail.
   ``There is evidence of drug use and abuse throughout this
case,'' Turck said. ``Both persons have been known to use drugs in
the past.''
   Police said Dawson and the victim were acquaintances. They were
both seen at a tavern last Monday night, and Miss Kithcart's body
was found the next day a few blocks away. The carving of Klan
initials on her leg was revealed by police last Thursday.
   Also charged in the case was Joseph Kiernan, 41, who police
described as a transient and former psychiatric patient. Kiernan,
who is white, was charged with sexually abusing the victim's corpse
and was jailed pending a psychological examination.
   Kiernan told a radio station in an interview last week that he
thought Miss Kithcart's body was a life-sized pornographic doll,
and that he called police when he saw a head wound.
   Police Chief James Riggens said investigators suspect the
letters may have been carved on the victim after she was killed.
   Police obtained a handwriting sample from Kiernan and were
awaiting test results to determine whether his handwriting matches
the writing style of the person who scratched ``KKK'' on Kithcart's
body, Assistant District Attorney John Prizzia said.
   Miss Kithcart's father told the Kingston Daily Freeman earlier
in the week that his daughter had fallen victim to drugs. ``I'm
almost positive it was a drug rub,'' Eugene Kithcart said.
   Preliminary autopsy results indicated Miss Kithcart was
strangled and struck on the head with a blunt instrument, police
said.
   Kingston is located about 25 miles north of Wappingers Falls, on
the opposite shore of Hudson River. Last November, 16-year-old
Tawana Brawley, of Wappingers Falls, was found with the letters
``KKK'' and racial epithets scrawled in a charcoal-like substance
on her skin after being missing for four days.
   She later said she had been abducted and raped by a group of
white men, but she and her family have refused to cooperate with a
state investigation.
</TEXT>
